From 0de57cdc2fe05b818595646c7f850db169169884 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yifan Zhang <yifan1.zhang@amd.com>
Date: Thu, 30 Apr 2026 15:47:57 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] drm/amdkfd: rate limit ioctl log

Reroute the per-ioctl entry debug print through dev_dbg_ratelimited()
so that workloads issuing very high-frequency KFD ioctls (queue
manipulation, alloc/free, suballoc) cannot drown the kernel ring
buffer when CONFIG_DYNAMIC_DEBUG flips this print on for triage.

Background
----------
With dev_dbg() active, a single inference iteration can emit thousands
of "ioctl cmd 0x... arg 0x..." lines per second. On hot reproducers
(e.g. sdma_suballoc_hang spawning >8k threads each calling
KFD_IOC_ALLOC_MEMORY_OF_GPU and KFD_IOC_FREE_MEMORY_OF_GPU back to
back) this fully saturates dmesg and obscures the real failure mode.

Switching to dev_dbg_ratelimited() preserves the diagnostic value of
the print (first few entries per second still recorded) while
preventing the loss of upstream/downstream messages around the actual
hang or crash window. The exit-side dev_dbg() print at line ~3899 is
kept as-is because it is gated by ret != 0 so it does not flood under
normal operation.

Tested on hjbog-srdc-22, MI308X, host kernel 5.10.134 + amdgpu DKMS
6.14.14 (V17.5 K-5 V2.3 stack). Confirmed dmesg no longer drowns under
sdma_suballoc_hang with -ECP=8192 -ETH=4 reproducer.

Cherry-picked from amd-staging-drm-next sha 0de57cdc2fe0.

Signed-off-by: Yifan Zhang <yifan1.zhang@amd.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdkfd/kfd_chardev.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdkfd/kfd_chardev.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdkfd/kfd_chardev.c
index c375a821c498..fd58085ac5df 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdkfd/kfd_chardev.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdkfd/kfd_chardev.c
@@ -3592,7 +3592,7 @@ static long kfd_ioctl(struct file *filep, unsigned int cmd, unsigned long arg)
 		goto err_i1;
 	}
 
-	dev_dbg(kfd_device, "ioctl cmd 0x%x (#0x%x), arg 0x%lx\n", cmd, nr, arg);
+	dev_dbg_ratelimited(kfd_device, "ioctl cmd 0x%x (#0x%x), arg 0x%lx\n", cmd, nr, arg);
 
 	/* Get the process struct from the filep. Only the process
 	 * that opened /dev/kfd can use the file descriptor. Child
